<h3>SECTION 2 - <u>CONFIDENTIALITY AND NON-DISCLOSURE</u></h3>

    <div class="pdf_page1_block3"><span>2.1</span> <u>Confidential</u> <u>Information</u> <u>and</u> <u>Trade</u> <u>Secrets</u>. Receiving Party agrees that all (i) Confidential Information, (ii) Trade Secrets, and (iii) all physical or electronic embodiments of the foregoing that are received or obtained by Receiving Party from Disclosing Party are confidential and are and will remain the sole and exclusive property of Disclosing Party. Receiving Party hereby expressly covenants and agrees that it will not, for or on behalf of Receiving Party or any Person, directly or indirectly, copy, use for Receiving Party’s own benefit or the benefit of any Person other than Disclosing Party or disclose to any Person, any Confidential Information or Trade Secrets. Upon termination of the Agreement for any reason, Receiving Party shall return (or at Disclosing Party’s written request, destroy) to Disclosing Party all things and documents containing Confidential Information or Trade Secrets (including physical or electronic copies of the foregoing) in Receiving Party’s possession, whether made by Receiving Party, its representatives or others, will be left with or returned to Disclosing Party. The parties agree that all right, title and interest in any improvements or developments to the Confidential Information or Trade Secrets, whether made by Disclosing Party, the Receiving Party, or jointly made by Disclosing Party and the Receiving Party, arising out of any disclosure of the Confidential Information or Trade Secrets by Disclosing Party to the Receiving Party is and shall remain solely the property of Disclosing Party. All “Confidential Information” subject to the provisions of this Section 2 must be either clearly marked as such or reasonably understood by the Receiving Party from the nature of its disclosure to be confidential. For purposes of the restrictions in this Section 2.1, (i) “Receiving Party” means Receiving Party, its Affiliates, and its and their respective directors, officers, employees, independent contractors, agents, attorneys and representatives, and (ii) Receiving Party shall cause all of the foregoing to be bound by the provisions hereof and be legally responsible if any of those parties breach the foregoing confidentiality and non-disclosure provisions.

